main event: A witness observed a potentially unidentified M shaped object with steady white lights in Kirksville, Missouri on January 20, 1967.
interesting points: The object was visible for about 5-10 minutes and appeared to shine lights toward the ground., The lights were described as red, gold, green, silver, and white., FAA reported no aircraft activity in the area at the time of the sighting., The observer, a pre-kindergarten teacher, was described as reliable with a master's degree in education., The object's flight path was horizontal and it circled to the west before disappearing.
witness description: A 50-year-old pre-kindergarten teacher with a master's degree in education.
